      "writtenOn": "2020-10-08T02:26:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "They are used to control the thread, kind of like thread::Cancelled() in the original library.\n\nThe thread/fiber/fiber.h is not available in emulator codebase, the most closer one is external/qemu/android/android-emu/android/base/threads/FunctorThread.h. But it doesn\u0027t provide the cancel() function.\n\ncarVhalReplayMsg is a MessageChannel, message in it can be shared between threads. It\u0027s very convenient to tell the while loop in the play thread to stop with MessageChannel.",
